Initital settings: 

Add a user Command follows:-
1. Add a new user using :- $useradd username
2.Create a password for the user:- $passwd username
3. terminal ask you for type password two time. After that it creates new user.
4.Password updated successfully.

Network Setting :- 
1.iP Address :- sudo ifconfig -a or  ifconfig

Display the list of services which are running:-  
1.Command:- $sudo systemctl -t=service --state=running

Stop and turn Off auto-start setting for a service if you don't need it:-
1. To start service: sudo systemctl start <service_name>
2. To stop service: sudo systemctl stop <service_name>
3. To enable service: sudo systemctl enable <service_name>


sudo setting:- 
Command:- sudo apt install package-name
